      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Proxmox Backups & Firewall Hardening</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mt-1">Feb 9, 2026</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4">Scheduled Backups</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-2 text-zinc-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Automated daily backups for the Jellyfin media server (VM 100) on Proxmox — scheduled at 21:00.</li>
        <li>Snapshot mode (no VM downtime during backup), ZSTD compression, stored on local 1.9 TB storage pool.</li>
        <li>Retention policy: keep last 1 backup. Email notifications configured for backup alerts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4">Firewall Hardening</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-2 text-zinc-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Locked down Proxmox host from fully open to LAN-only access. Default inbound policy set to DROP, outbound to ACCEPT.</li>
        <li>Created a <code class="text-sm bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">localnet</code> alias for the LAN subnet (192.168.86.0/24) at the datacenter level.</li>
        <li>Host: SSH (22) and Proxmox Web UI (8006) — allowed from LAN only. Everything else dropped.</li>
        <li>VM 100 (Jellyfin): Jellyfin (8096) and SSH (22) — allowed from LAN only. Everything else dropped.</li>
        <li>Disabled rpcbind (port 111) — an unnecessary NFS-related service that was listening on the host.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

